                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111N39/72</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-29T11:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 1.55 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7832. Your 5895, November 24, 3 p.m. <persName corresp="#p_CLR1">Lord Robert
                        Cecil</persName>, in charge Foreign Office during <persName
                        corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName>’s absence in Paris, informs me that his
                    Government has no objection to such a declaration by Government of the United
                    States, but he thinks it better that all principal Allied powers should make
                    such a declaration at same time if any make it. A declaration by one great power
                    might suggest suspicion that others were not willing to make declaration. He
                    declared the British Government quite willing to make declaration and he
                    expressed hope that the French would also.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
